{"id":"adjective-tn-8","label":"Types of Adjectives","lockAfter":3,"list":[{"type":"selectWord","label":"Identify - Adjective of Quality","id":"select-quality","data":{"title":"Click and select the adjective of quality in the below sentence.","text":"Kolkata is a *large* city.\nHe is an *honest* man.\nThe *foolish old* crow tried to sing.\nThis is the Grammar of the *English* language."}},{"type":"selectWord","label":"Identify - Adjective of Quantity","id":"select-quantity","data":{"title":"Identify the adjective of quantity in the below sentence.","text":"I ate *some* rice.\nHe showed *much* patience.\nHe has *little* intelligence.\nWe have had *enough* exercise.\nHe has lost *all* his wealth.\nYou have *no* sense.\nHe did not eat *any* rice.\nTake *great* care of your health.\nHe claimed his *half* share of the booty.\nThere has not been *sufficient* rain this year.\nThe *whole* sum was expended."}},{"type":"selectWord","label":"Identify - Adjective of Number","id":"select-number","data":{"title":"Identify the adjective of number in the below sentence.","text":"Each hand has *five* fingers.\n*Few* cats like cold water.\nThere are *no* pictures in this book.\nI have taught you *many* things.\n*All* men must die.\nHere are *some* ripe mangoes.\n*Most* boys like cricket.\nThere are *several* mistakes in your exercise.\nSunday is the *first* day of the week."}},{"type":"selectWord","label":"Identify - Demonstrative Adjective","id":"select-demonstrative","data":{"title":"Identify the demonstrative adjective in the below sentence.","text":"*This* lady is stronger than Maha.\n*That* boy is industrious.\n*These* books are good.\n*Those* girls must be encouraged."}},{"type":"selectWord","label":"Identify - Interrogative Adjective","id":"select-interrogative","data":{"title":"Identify the interrogative adjective in the below sentence.","text":"*What* colour dress was the man in?\n*Which* way shall we go?\n*Whose* book is this?"}},{"label":"Classify Adjective","type":"classifySentence","id":"select","commonData":{"title":"Classify the type of adjective for the underlined word.","types":["Adjective of Quality","Adjective of Quantity","Adjective of Number","Demonstrative Adjective","Interrogative Adjective"]},"data":[["Kolkata is a *large* city.","I ate *some* rice.\nHe showed *much* patience.\nHe has *little* intelligence.\nWe have had *enough* exercise.","Each hand has *five* fingers.\n*Few* cats like cold water.\nThere are *no* pictures in this book.","*This* lady is stronger than Maha.","*What* colour dress was the man in?"],["He is an *honest* man.","He has lost *all* his wealth.\nYou have *no* sense.\nHe did not eat *any* rice.\nTake *great* care of your health.","I have taught you *many* things.\n*All* men must die.\nHere are *some* ripe mangoes.","*That* boy is industrious.","*Which* way shall we go?"],["The *foolish old* crow tried to sing.\n            This is the Grammar of the *English* language.","He claimed his *half* share of the booty.\nThere has not been *sufficient* rain this year.\nThe *whole* sum was expended.","*Most* boys like cricket.\nThere are *several* mistakes in your exercise.\nSunday is the *first* day of the week.","*These* books are good.\n            Those* girls must be encouraged.","*Whose* book is this?"]]}]}